  "texts": [
    "The rule specifies monitoring the 'loss' function, with a mode of 'min' and a patience of 'Pat'.",
    "This rule checks whether the loss function on the training data stops decreasing at the end of each epoch.",
    "If it continues for an additional 'Pat' epochs, the training is halted.",
    "To mitigate overfitting, dropout and L2 regularization were incorporated at each hidden layer, while only L2 regularization applied to the output layer.",
    "L2 regularization penalizes the loss function (e.g., sum of squared error loss) by adding the sum of squared weights multiplied by a regularization parameter (l)."
  ],
